  <div class="tab-pane fade" id="unit01-intro-tabs-tips" role="tabpanel">
    <ul class="mb-0">
      <li class="mb-2">You rarely use more than two or three adjectives before a noun in natural speech. Long strings of adjectives sound formal or literary.</li>
      <li class="mb-2">A useful memory aid: <strong>OSASCOMP</strong> — Opinion, Size, Age, Shape, Colour, Origin, Material, Purpose.</li>
      <li class="mb-2">Quantity words (numbers, <em>many</em>, <em>few</em>) always come first, before opinion adjectives.</li>
      <li class="mb-2">Purpose adjectives are often nouns being used attributively: <em>a sleeping bag</em>, <em>a writing desk</em>.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
